Qt 5.7 introduces many new features and improvements as well as bugfixes
over the 5.6.x series. For more details, refer to the online documentation
included in this distribution. The documentation is also available online:

  http://doc.qt.io/qt-5/index.html

The Qt version 5.7 series is binary compatible with the 5.6.x series.
Applications compiled for 5.6 will continue to run with 5.7.

Some of the changes listed in this file include issue tracking numbers
corresponding to tasks in the Qt Bug Tracker:

  https://bugreports.qt.io/

Each of these identifiers can be entered in the bug tracker to obtain more
information about a particular change.

****************************************************************************
*                          Controls                                        *
****************************************************************************

 - General
   * [QTBUG-35754] Enabled using the module in statically built applications.
   * Added support for a QT_QUICK_CONTROLS_1_STYLE environment variable,
     which takes priority over the existing variable QT_QUICK_CONTROLS_STYLE.
     This allows specifying system wide style name preferences separately for
     Qt Quick Controls 1 and 2.

 - CheckBox and RadioButton
   * Added support for tooltips

 - ScrollView
   * [QTBUG-41591] Fixed an issue that caused scroll bars to be non-
     interactive on desktop platforms with touch screens.

 - Slider
   * [QTBUG-35972] Fixed wheel scrolling direction when using natural
     scrolling direction on OS X.

****************************************************************************
*                          Dialogs                                         *
****************************************************************************

 - General
   * [QTBUG-45868] Enabled using the module in statically built applications.

****************************************************************************
*                          Layouts                                         *
****************************************************************************

 - General
